{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "615454d7248e1e84597dd6cf", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba3"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "24", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "The diffraction pattern of a single slit is shown in the figure. The point at which the path difference of the extreme rays is two times the wavelength is<br />\r<br />\r<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/nta_abhyas/neet/images/ikbcjrtnpmykknwrnxjbxagztqysawrqorhqywyfrqorpvkkdt.png\" />", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "g4Ir3", "text": "point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "J6f5G", "text": "point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "pWeMr", "text": "point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "dD2xm", "text": "point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "In diffraction of light at a single slit, the pattern obtained consists of a central bright band having alternate dark and bright bands of decreasing intensity on both sides.<br /><br />For n<sup>th&nbsp;</sup>minima (secondary),<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03b8</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>n\u03bb</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&nbsp;</mi></math><br /><br />For n<sup>th</sup> maxima (secondary),<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03b8</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03bb</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br />Thus, point <math><mn>5</mn></math> corresponds to the path difference of extreme rays equal to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03bb</mi></math>.<br /><br /><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/nta_abhyas/neet/images/jksxbechrvzrluifslhiexhyrjnetfjdgfoslatrhwgkaobzoe.png\" />", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["61e7bd71ba5ea0509a0032eb", "61602441a74735a290c2b9d8", "6160244116d221a133c08775", "61602442734cc2aca48335d5", "61bb8210dae5f7af9600d5d0", "61964c933923ea685eb30f0b", "6160243f6067541f280c4e8f", "6160243e17040ba6b8d61b88", "61c08989c653cc4ca7b56e9e", "61964c9222879be3883b609e", "62962125b6ad3169b0d85632", "629109f2bf97d58ac676959b", "629f390f8db6a438ffb8c25b", "629f3a93a12e7977